Part 2
Once a pathway has been reforced/reinforced/reforged/fortified under siege/burrow or whatever may be the case it will be reinstituted under immediate construction/rebuild.
This is to stabilize a compromised/incursive area.
This is out of necessity during which this will improve conditions/quality-of-life/luxury/ease-of-access/affordances and diminish threats/affairs etc. (this includes triggers/reactives)
It was only because of the outbreak at the highest stages that this way needed, it was a complex that was put off for a long time, and mentioned only as optional/subroutes, to help protect/assist during difficulties/instabilities/turbulences/tumultevity etc.
It is now assessed for every stage of any chapter in its extent/depth of coverage.

This is basically an OMNI-INSTITUTE/ZEROMAX-SYSTEM
